div1.p:
It appear'd by the Evidence, That the House was uninhabited, a Padlock being upon the Door, and the Prisoner being seen loitering about the House, and at last got in;
Seth Ward
watching him, went and acquainted those who kept the Key, and going to the House, they found the Padlock taken off, and the Prisoner in the House, who pretended he went in to ease himself.
